The paper deals with image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the bias in CNNs, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
